docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — For more than a year, Amazon searched for a second headquarters, a home to as many as 50,000 workers that would be coequal to its current home in Seattle. Instead, Amazon is closing in on deals to split what it called HQ2 into two locations, according to people briefed on the discussions. The company appears ready to move to Long Island City in Queens, according to two of the people. It is also close to a deal to move to a spot in Arlington, Va., just across the Potomac River from Washington, one of the people said.

headline.main: What We Don’t Know About Amazon’s Split HQ2

docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — When Texas officials pushed Amazon to pay nearly $270 million in back sales taxes in 2010, Amazon responded by closing its only warehouse in the state and scrapping expansion plans there.
